OL,6,F"Had this public area been better
OL,7,Fmanaged, this death might have been
OL,8,Favoided. No lessons were learned from
OL,9,Fthe limb falling off the tree less
OL,10,Fthan a year before. Cheshire East
OL,11,FCouncil had not adopted a formal
OL,12,Foverarching tree strategy to manage
OL,13,Fthe risks from trees in public places
OL,14,Fsince it was formed in 2009.
OL,16,F"There was no overarching, consistent
OL,17,Frisk identification process leading to
OL,18,Fzoning of trees in all frequently
OL,19,Faccessed public areas.
